Tomorrow’s State of the Nation Address will be Cyril Ramaphosa’s fourth since 2018 and by far the most expectant yet. But with sluggish business confidence, unemployment rate at levels last seen in 2008 and Eskom in deeper crisis than ever before and no solution in sight, what will the president actually say tomorrow? CNBC Africa’s Karabo Letlhatlha spoke to the voice of Business, CEO of Business Leadership South Africa, Busisiwe Mavuso.